The Star Guild Award for Best Film (previously known as the Apsara Award for Best Film) is given by the producers of the film and television guild as part of its annual award ceremony to recognise the best film of the year. Following its inception in 2004, no one was awarded in 2005 and 2007.

== Winner and nominees ==

=== 2000s ===
2004 Koi... Mil Gaya - Filmkraft - Rakesh Roshan
Baghban - B.R. Films - B.R. Chopra
Gangaajal - Prakash Jha Productions - Prakash Jha
Kal Ho Naa Ho - Dharma Productions - Yash Johar, Karan Johar
